place_description: Upscale grocery store chain with an old-world vibe offers local produce, prepared eats, wine & more.

reviews_data.review_text: Every single Friday morning, that I come here the cashier white blonde hair older side. stares at me and who ever I come with up and down and I can come in and we can say good morning and she will ignore the good morning and when she hands us the receipt and we say thankyou have a great day she will look the other way and not say anything. Feels very uncomfortable we come here a lot shop at this fresh market and the one in pineville a lot and we never get this type of treatment anywhere else but here.

Recently picked up some chicken cutlets, ground sirloin and some produce.  Made a nice chicken salad.  Both of us got terribly sick that night and the next day to day and a half.  I was suspicious of the chicken as I ate it but I had cooked it thoroughly and I trusted the Fresh Market.  However now I am far more wary.  We are certain that the chicken had been mishandled.  Planning to take the chicken and some of the produce (used in the chicken salad) back today but I haven't seen a manager in this store in a couple of years.

Fresh market needs to fix this situation and also make sure that their managers are present on the floor and available for issues.
The staff is amazing!!!! The ladies in the Bakery and Deli are phenomenal and front end is very pleasant and kind.

This store has excellent quality products. As soon as you enter, you will see beautiful flowers and foliage. In the fruit and vegetable section, you will find a wide variety of quality products; the store has a wide variety of Kombuchas and natural juices. Don't forget to check out the bakery and the pond cakes.

I love this place it has my favorite food and has really kind workers and there's not many people there so that makes it just very quick to get your food done
so overall, it's my favorite store to go to. I definitely recommend to go to it.

"Mr. Glen"...

Today I went to this store, and I had a question about measuring one product, this gentleman(Mr. Glen) was on the floor, when I approached him with my question, instead of receiving a friendly answer I received a "cold" treatment from him, just making me feel so bad for asking. I believe that customer service involves all, from a friendly face, manners, and tone of voice.
Love this place! So many organic and non-gmo, while caught seafood. Love their prepared salads, baked goods, coffee and Organic ice cream! The Meyer Lemon Cookie was FANTASTIC!

My husband and I shop fresh Market on providence road.
Ashley in the deli is amazing!!!!
Patience and kindness.

Shopping here is a very laid back and relaxing experience. Maybe I'm always in on the less-busy hours but all I see are hard working employees and a large variety of prepared foods. Need a charcuterie board liketysplit? They got it and the price isn't bad either. Sushi was also good and I'll definitely have to try more.

They also had ready-bake pizzas that looked great. Did I mention the friendly staff? I usually shop at Costco but the variety here is perfect. They had like 20 different wholesale coffees. The cheese monger was a real surprise. I love The Fresh Market!
Such a disappointment, going here for great quality products and unwrapping them up only to see how old they are!
This Fresh Market is really nice. It's big and open and well organized.  The women in the bakery are so nice and always make me feel very appreciated. Will always shop here!!

Feeling like there are issues at this location.   Management issues?   Not sure.  I definitely find the cashiers are particularly zoned out.   They do not engage with the customers.  Not really rude per se but just not friendly.   Deli and meat counter people are fine..... helpful and friendly.   Just something about the cashiers....that's why I'm thinking it's a scheduling or management issue.

Really disappointed to see that I paid for nearly 1/2lb of water and packaging when buying a 2+lb package of fresh chicken breasts.  They put something underneath the chicken that absorbs water/juices.  Perhaps they are injecting the chicken with water?  What else would create that much excess water?  So I paid 20% more per pound because of this.
Went in for my sesame stix fix and some wine! Had a long talk with Janice who works there, she's a hoot!
Excellent food, friendly and knowledgeable staff.
Love this market, ready to eat or prepare your own food. Very good quality and selection.

Fresh Market is a very focused format on specific products that are unique, fresh and healthy.
The deterrent would be the prices for many.
The staff is well informed and very helpful!

Finally had the chance to walk the store. While it can be a little pricey where some items are less elsewhere, I enjoyed meeting Laura and Celine. I bought a delicious stuffed cabbage, balsamic glaze for a prosciutto salad as well as feta cheese and spring mix. All were delicious and fresh. The fish and meat Depts are immaculate and have wonderful product!  I will return to try other items you just can't get elsewhere. Glad this store is nearby!  Parking is plentiful as well.
Recently the service has been subpar.  I will no longer shop this store or any of them locally.  Too many choices in Charlotte
Laziest bakery in the world 8:45 still no fresh bread.. way to live up to the name

Love this store! Everyone is always so helpful. When you walk in, there are so many beautiful flowers greeting you that it is very welcoming.  The deals are amazing, and not many people know about their rotisserie chicken meal or the free crossiants you get when you buy the chicken salad.  Let's not forget the chuck and chicken special every Tuesday!!  Just love this store!

Always dependable quality food choices. Watch for quality daily specials.

Friendly and helpful staff.
Excellent produce, butcher, seafood, deli and bakery.  I just love the place. The store manager is very personable and friendly and always greets you.

Always a delight, my visits to The Fresh Market result in treasure I mine from pristine and vibrantly colored displays of fruit, veggies, herbs, aged cheeses and on and on. And their garlic butter chicken is amazing!!!!!

Chelsea is the reason I shop at this particular Fresh Market . She is knowledgeable, helpful and friendly! I cannot say enough about Chelsea. She is an exceptional employee.
Martha is also a great employee! She is always running around and working hard. She takes the time to help me find things with a smile on her face.
Zack is always going the extra mile to look for specific brand yogurts for me.
Friendly and welcoming. Nice and clean.
Great shopping experience today all i wanted available.
LOVE their selection of pre made fresh food!!! Great tasting and many, many selections. It's like Zabar's in NYC

No one can beat the freshness and quality there have here IMO. Got an absolutely delicious filet and fresh asparagus for date night and it knocked it out of the park! Update: still the freshest, best quality meat and produce!
Good place to stop at if your in a rush. Their deserts and variety of milks are good quality

Catching up on reviews. I was at The Fresh Market on Monday, 05-02-22 when I tried these pineberries for the first time. They were on sale for $5. Lately, I'll stop in to see if anything good is on sale when I go to the Hallmark nearby. The items are expensive. I will sometimes find different flavors of certain products here that I don't see in other places. This is one of the other places I can find pineapple tepache. The pineberries were different. I may try them again if they were on sale.
Deli was very helpful (thanks)
Always nice..
Love Fresh Market. Prices are high so there's only certain items we purchase from there. Nice to browse through though.
Very delicious food. I love food shopping here
The monthly deal are.great and the pre made meals have saved us the what's for dinner question a ton!

Bought 1 1/2 lbs fresh cooked turkey breast for $20. When I got and had the turkey for dinner it tasted like 5 day old turkey after Thanksgiving. It was disgusting!! I will go back with receipt and demand a full refund!
Nice place but pricey and very few good sales
Always friendly and helpful staff and they always have what I need.
The beat place in town to get fresh, dark, ground turkey meat. They have some other things I buy as well, but that's the draw for me. Prefer not to see so many flowers though.

After driving to FRESH Foods to purchase our favorite chili starter mix and decided to purchase the ground beef meat as well because it's supposed to be fresh per their store statement, my wife started preparing the meat and was shocked to find fresh red meat wrapped around old brown meat.  Called the store to complain but no one answered.  So now I'm posting this complaint.  Will never buy meat from them ever again.
Good choices of food!
By far my favorite place to buy meat. Great selection. Always clean and friendly staff.
I just love browsing the store. I often don't need much as far as groceries but I always find something tasty to take home.
Wonderful as always! Great food and great staff.
It was excellent great customer service .The products are in stock as well that's s a plus.
Nice place arr good people
Very clean friendly staff , large selection. Only complaint it's little pricey ..
Great veggies and produce.   I find unique fruit like mandarin oranges which I rarely see at other grocers.  Such a treat.  They stock many brands of spring water.
Doesn't have the food selection it used to pre-covid.
Excellent customer service.  Very clean and well stocked.  Larger than some of the other stores, still very nice layout and easy to navigate.
Always great staff here friendly and welcome to help
Everyone who works here is so pleasant and nice. Store is always clean and well stocked. I love the bowtie pesto pasta salad -- so good
Always a pleasure to shop here. Helpful staff, everything is well presented.
Fantastic people with a plethora of options. Tracy was fantastic and helped me find delicious items for my wife who is GF and dairy free. Thank you all so much.
Love his store...
Well thought out plan for Easter -- pick up was like the Army!

Kind of Grocery store you can definitely pleasantly waste time in!! Bakery section offers a good bit of variety! Deli, Meat, and Cheese options are ALWAYS amazing!! Definitely offers some really delicious and unique offerings in pantry goods, frozen food, beer, and wine! Much larger than option the one on Pineville-Matthews road, or Providence Rd.

There today to buy the fish and chips for a family of four,  There was no frech fries or cole slaw went to Deli Nice young Black man behind the Deli Helps us with the cole slaw and went to get french fries, Such a very nice gentleman and we need more people like him, Went out of his way to make sure we had what we needed. Thanks so much! His name was Ezekiel.

Love shopping at The Fresh Market.  Fresh vegetables and fruits, great seafood section, and their Market Meal Kits are delicious and easy. One note on beef used in meal kits:  it must be tenderized or it is impossible to eat.
Their fresh flower display is beautiful!
Meal deals are awsome
Have not been to fresh market in forever.  Never disappointed.  Always great food and selection. Got crab cakes. So good!

Flowers
And they last forever
Excellent prices on a dozen roses $35 for Valentine's Day
Great alternative to Whole Foods, although the bakery's treats at other locations seem more abundant.
Good selection of quality foods

Every year I purchase a port crown roast and have been very satisfied with the quality of meat and presentation of the roast. This year, due to covid 19 my table will not be full  of guests. I ordered a 4 bone. When I opened it I was surprised to find a slab of meat laying on its side. There were 4 bones but one was broken. The roast was not Frenched as in the past. Therefore, the roast will not end up looking like years in the past. I pride in having a nice looking table but this piece of meat is terrible looking. All I can hope is that the taste is as before
Always the best service and selection at the meat counter. These guys really know their stuff!  Can't find decent skirt steaks anywhere but here!  Great staff!
Nice & crowded but everyone is social distancing.

My new favorite grocery store! Esp love the weekly take and bake dinner specials. What a deal! Staff are super friendly and helpful, store is super clean with great selections. I'll be a repeat customer.
Well stocked,good quality and high prices.
Wow . Perfect turkey dinner.  Everything was great!!!! Loved your cranberry sauce. One of the best turkeys we have had. So moist!
Pricey. But amazing selection. Ambience superb.
Nice store. Great deli and butcher very fresh and friendly. Will shop here again.
Wow'
The best candy corn is found here.
Best lighting. Fresh and easy. Little big meal is unbeatable.
Unique ... an adventure
Great food and store is awesome

I shop here once a week and everything I've tried has been wonderful. We usually get fresh beef and chicken. The stuffed chicken is always amazing. And the staff is always so friendly.
The bakery is top notch. Seems very clean too.
We've had the 20 minute meals and yes they are a little pricey, but it's literally everything I need in one box.
Just tried the wraps from the deli this week- so good!
And I love love love the strawberry orange juice!!
No diet juices but lots of healthy choices
Their bakery is top Knotch.

We love going to Fresh Market. Walking into the store is like taking comfort food out of the oven. The smell of Fresh Market is rejuvenating. I cannot say that about any other grocery store I've ever visited. I don't really get it.

Prices are slightly higher than Publix or HT, but so is the quality. I drive past Whole Foods to get here and I've been a Prime customer for ages.  Dang, I need an excuse to go here now...
Love this store.Very helpful staff ,easy to find items
Nice location
I wish we had one closer to north NJ! Very helpful team members.

This place is great. Their bakery items are really good, and the bakery has great service. This place is a little upscale, but it's worth going to! Check it out at least once! Great parking in large front lot. While you're there, stop at Total Wines and Home Depot.

Disappointing! Seems like they had some malnourished whole cooked chickens for sale, not many precooked meals available by the pound like other Fresh Markets have. Stuff didn't look very appetizing. I thought they'd all be the same but I guess I was wrong.

When I first walked into the store, an employee greeted me with "fresh off the block," whatever that means.  The only thing I truly enjoyed about my visit was when I approached the meat counter.  Eric had exceptional customer service.   He was able to enlighten me of some of the perks of keeping up with emails through the Fresh Market Program.  Laura, my cashier, did not greet me when approaching the register and was throwing my glass milk cartoon around.  I had to ask if she broke anything, she rudely replied, "NO."  It was near the end of my order, and I sarcastically said, "Well, hey, how are you?" because she never opened her mouth to say a word to me.  This transaction took place at around 8:00 pm on 07/01/2020.  Very disgusted at what Laura believed what "customer service" is and mainly frustrated at the management (Mark Catapano) for allowing an employee to treat their guest with such disrespect. Perhaps, during your next team meeting or before store opening and closings- coaching your staff on the do's and don't's of customer service is highly recommended.

I was at this location last week getting groceries for a customer and some of the workers wouldn't help me find some of the items I was looking for. To top it off the cashier didn't even greet me and didn't wanna hand me my recipe. Not the type of service ANYONE deserves. If I could give this location less than a star I would
The food was good.
Helpful staff and nice selection. Pricey
Healthly options all around

The Floral Dept is the Best.  Needed flowers for Last Minute table setting.  JANICE saved the dinner party!!! She was so helpful and patient with me. I will now only get flowers from Fresh Market.  Much better than any of the floral shops here in Ballantyne area.
Fresh Market,  Janice is awesome!!!
As always a great Fresh Market - everything just as expected - or better.
Love the Fresh Market! I shop for all my specialty items.
Great selection of food and courteous employees.

Luv this place! I wish they would open another one in Concord. There is an Earth Fare that is closing in a week and wish The Fresh Market would take its place. It is on Christenberry. The clientele is perfect for a Fresh Market. Pls
Great ground beef on Tuesday.

It was ok!  Have been going to Fresh Market from when they opened the very first store in Charlotte many years ago.  Seems the quality and service at least this store has declined.  It does seem as they grow they have lost sight of or rather out of touch with the customer.
I like coming here because it is never busy. Unfortunately the prices are a little high and I can't always find everything I need, but it's worth it for the easy parking and short lines.

Went into this establishment for the very first time. Spent 15 minutes in there and passed 4 different associates. All of which did not acknowledge me nor did they ask if I needed assistance.  Reached the register, greeted the clerk, she ignored my greeting and turned her back to me the entire transaction. Did not turn my way until she needed to hand me my receipt. Completely disgusted, I will be sure not to return.
What a RIDICULOUSLY awesome bone in ribeye. $9.99 a lb! I bought ALL THEY HAD

High End, High Touch Shopping Experience.
Incredibly varied selection: deep, wide and value-based. High quality offerings in every department and a staff that is exceptionally well trained and sincerely helpful. It takes hard work to pull all of that off and make it seem effortless.
Highly recommended.

We have always ordered our beef tenderloin for family gatherings and holidays at Fresh market. We recently moved to Charlotte and our Thanksgiving order was perfect however, our Christmas tenderloin was terrible, I preordered a 6 lbs and when I went to pick up our order was handed an 8 lbs, not big deal if the filet would have been good, however after cooked and sliced we realized I paid almost 130.00 dollars for a piece of fat with some meat. The worst experience thus far when ordering from them. I'm listing publicly as I have tried to contact management to let them know, I don't want a refund I just want them to be aware that quality control perhaps failed this time around, but I have been kept on hold endless minutes and haven't been able to reach anyone who would listen. Very disappointed with our recent order.

Love the chicken salad here, it's just great. And usually you buy a pound of it for $10 and you get a box of 4 great croissants for free, I've came to this and other fresh markets just for that deal many times. Then on Christmas Eve this year, I find out that the deal is suspended for the holidays. What? What kind of crazy thing is that lol. Doesn't seem to be a higher demand for the product at that time, or a shortage of croissants at that time of year. So it just seems petty to stop offering it? An explanation would help. Thanks

Edited due to reply

Thanks for replying April. I can understand that. I would challenge your group to look at wether certain specials really would impact in a negative way any holiday business above normal business, and I would doubt it to be so. So it probably costs more to suspend the specials than not to, imo. But I appreciate the reply and explanation!
past 2 times i have been i was overcharged on several items.. They said they would send me a gift card but never received it.
Great flowers, great meat department,  great store
They have some nice products but a lot of the same products you can get for much less other places. The customer service has gone done hill recently.

The market itself is great.
The cashier not so much. After my third visit ,
I just feel like I am disturbing them. No smile, nothing.

Great, fresh, quality, meats and an upscale grocery selection.  Eclectic  choices of not-so-common items makes the visit endearing.  Lebkuchen, straight from Nurnberg, Germany available 'til Christmas.  Beer and wine in quantity and various countries available.  Parking available.  Clean restrooms.  Coffee samples.  Lots to See, Explore, Contemplate, Buy, and Enjoy.
This place is really great!
Clear store. The selection is great.
They're a little big meal is the best kept secret in Charlotte. You can feed a family of four for $20.
Who ever uses the store microphone needs to talk not yell like a fog horn volume. Ouch my ears  try not to shop here again!
First time at Fresh Market...great experience.  Clean store; helpful associates; produce, prepared foods, meats and seafood presented well and looked (and tasted) fresh.
Great place to shop. The butcher's section is handled beautifully. This place has shown that eating fresh and healthy does not have to cost an arm and a leg.
Fresh ingredients and good selection to choose from.
Organized and clean store. It's almost ever busy. Lots of parking spaces.
Clean and well stocked. Some interesting varieties of things.
Great high end food shopping. Clean store.
Great service

This place is amateur hour. They screw up every holiday order, and just today I waited in line 20 minutes for checkout. Two people working the registers on Memorial Day weekend? What kind of Mickey Mouse operation is your GM running over there? Would have given this place a half star if it was an option. Not worry of even a one star rating.
Very nice lady who waited on me in the Deli section. Wish I had asked her name. Made Korean wings for me.
Wonderful fresh food, including product, meats, ready-made lunches & a nice variety of all products.
I love this store. Great selection of quality products at good prices. The baked goods are the best, especially the croissants.

Friendly service, but every single time I have shopped here, 3/4 of my fruit purchased are bad and/or moldy.  I mentioned that to them on my third return and they did not seem to care other than to say sorry.  Won't be shopping here again; why would I pay premium prices for subpar products?

We ordered through their online website two trays of specialty wraps for my dad's surprise birthday party. They were a big hit!! Very well prepared and portioned as well as delicious. The staff were professional and extremely helpful and polite. Thank you for helping us to make our party awesome!
Store is clean, employees friendly, hate that they no longer have the "Little Big Meal" in the front center of the store.
Excellent service and selection of products.
Healthy eating habits
Nice selection
This is a great alternative to Whole Foods around the corner.
One of my favorite markets. Everyone is friendly and always ready to help.
Great selection of meat and produce

Very clean, good quality produce, excellent customer service at meat counter, customer service available on floor, plenty of parking, bright environment, love the thick cut Market bacon...not too salty. Will be back.
Very neat and great foods and , flowers , deli and bake awesome
I ate tuna  fish  salad, cheese, grapes and crackers it was  delicious!
$20 dinner.....fabulous idea, fabulous food.
Bad price s
Wonderful gem of a grocery store!

Goat kefir, plain, was short dated (today).
No bean sprouts or broccoli sprouts available .
Great grocery store, warm friendly associates. Always good deals
Great store. Bigger and better than any other Fresh Market I have been to. Well worth shopping at.

Way too expensive, e.g. $8.58 for a loaded baked potato.  Other than maybe an occasional meat or other sale item I won't shop here.

Take Trader Joe's prices and add at least 20-60% more.

Alexa, thx for your response -- the issue is pretty straightforward, i.e. Fresh Market prices are just way too high.  Trader Joe's prices are much lower for comparable items, with no difference in quality.
Love their butcher shop!

WoW. I was so surprised when such poor customer service was provided at this wonderful supermarket I loved (passed tense). I feel betrayed. No wonder brick and mortar locations are going out of business. The store did look very empty. Wish them luck but I'll be shopping elsewhere.

They have a great selection of natural and organic products. Their produce is a little on the expensive side. Every week they have a $20 meal deal. It is a 4 serving with 5 different items; a protein, vegetable, side, sometimes dessert or bread. A GREAT deal!
Good quality groceries at reasonable prices. More eclectic choices than other grocery stores
My mom loves this place
Can get pricey gotta find your deals.
Just over priced sorry to say!
Love there meat and seafood selection
Truly they have the best product in town. Staffs are friendly and helpful.
Excellent grocery stores
Valentine's Day Dinner Special-- I would not recommend this to anyone.  The portion sizes were small and the lobster tail smelled bad.  Not impressed at all.  Wasted $50 today.
Good service. Good products. Always pleased!
I like it here, better than Wholefoods.

The store is filled with great products. However,  the customer service is consistently the worst.  I asked one worker if she was the one who was going to make my sandwich and she snarled, "when I'm done making my pizza"   .  There was noone waiting for a pizza and no need to be so rude. I have ordered sandwiches on several occasions and never do they get the order correct or deliver within a reasonable amount of time. Waiting over 30 mins for 4 sandwiches (only got three) is absurd.  When I asked for my fourth sandwich the response was, "oh someone else must have taken it"  .  After that dismissal the employee walked away!!!  Thank God Whole Foods opened up. They understand that the customer not only wants a good product but helpful and competent service too.  If you want an occasional smile or a friendly greeting or if you want basic competent service you will not find it here. I have looked and since they opened I am yet to find it.
Always love going to Fresh Market
Fresh veggies and great ready made foods.

Fresh market truly has the best meat in town, great cheese selections as well as healthy fruit and vegetables. The store is clean and everyone is so friendly. I love going there and finding new things to try.
very friendly and always there to help when needed
I love this store. It's better than going to an amusement park! Gorgeous produce, helpful employees, great selection! Try their little bag of "heavenly" tomatoes! Their name suits them perfectly!
Wonderful selection of produce, baked items.  The butcher case always impresses.  The staff at every location are very knowledgeable and happy.
Nice fruit tart
Excellent Meats
Logan is very professional and personable
$20 meal deal is awesome
Convenient but overpriced. Deli is gross.
The store is filthy!
Love the little big meal each week
Good place to shop and there and great works. The meat the dept is the best.
Very clean. Large selection of organic produce.
Excellent food.  I especially like the weekly dinner-for-4 specials.  The service is adequate but not always the best.
Good variety of both savory,sweet and wine.  A little bit pricey.

The meat counter has only No-Antibiotic meat.  Wow!  That one tweak in my buying habits will yield great results over time, I think.  Great store, great deli items, and even everyday-basics come in their own brand, which I like.  And remember, always make friends with your Butcher!
Great place
Nice Fresh Market. Larger than most.

Ordered beef filet for Christmas and when I arrived at store it was all packaged up so could not see it.  It was much larger and more expensive than I had asked for and was not cleaned/trimmed as they said they would do.  Had lots of pieces tied together.  I am very disappointed!

I'm very pleased with the new Fresh Market in S. Charlotte. If there were any inconsistencies upon opening the new store, it was quickly remedied. The prepared foods are great. The fruit is delicious. I love the party trays and holiday meals. I have one BIG issue that will deter me from going to Fresh Market. There are no areas in the parking lot in which to leave the empty carts. Therefore, when I'm not well, hurting or the weather is in climate, what to do with the empty cart? I'm certainly not going to walk all the way back to the store. I shouldn't have to. Therefore, I can NOT patronize or I can leave the cart to float around the lot rolling into cars like my car was dented by a run away cart driven by the wind. It's an easy fix, spend a few $$$ to install cart holders.

Produce was terrible.  Purchased Red Delicious apples and they were mush inside, I could crush it with my hand they were so mushy.  Ended up throwing the other 3 away.  A bit pricey for food you can get cheaper at other supermarkets.
